1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:08,146 --> 00:00:14,285
1995, APRIL 26

3
00:00:14,352 --> 00:00:16,087
Minoru, you're so slow!

4
00:00:16,621 --> 00:00:17,989
Makoto!

5
00:00:18,056 --> 00:00:19,524
Wait!

6
00:00:24,028 --> 00:00:29,400
1995, APRIL 26

7
00:00:40,245 --> 00:00:41,513
Hey, Minoru.

8
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:44,549
What do you want to be when you grow up?

9
00:00:49,087 --> 00:00:50,155
A ninja!

10
00:00:50,221 --> 00:00:51,055
A ninja?

11
00:00:51,122 --> 00:00:52,757
What about you?

12
00:00:56,694 --> 00:00:57,829
I…

13
00:00:57,896 --> 00:00:59,264
don't really know.

14
00:01:05,136 --> 00:01:06,237
Bam!

15
00:01:11,943 --> 00:01:14,812
It hurts!

16
00:01:14,879 --> 00:01:17,115
Mom! Dad! Minoru's…

17
00:01:40,205 --> 00:01:47,111
2010, APRIL 27

18
00:01:53,284 --> 00:01:55,086
-Minoru, hold that side.
-Okay.

19
00:01:56,788 --> 00:02:03,428
2010, APRIL 27

20
00:02:08,399 --> 00:02:09,601
Moving on to our next story.

21
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:12,203
The Diet has passed a bill today

22
00:02:12,270 --> 00:02:16,040
to abolish the statute of limitations
for heinous crimes, such as murder.

23
00:02:16,608 --> 00:02:20,111
And this evening, it was put
into effect with unusual speed.

24
00:02:21,212 --> 00:02:25,216
Under this bill, crimes for which
the statute of limitations has expired

25
00:02:25,283 --> 00:02:28,219
cannot have this statute
retroactively abolished.

26
00:02:28,786 --> 00:02:30,788
As a result, cases from April 27, 2010,

27
00:02:30,855 --> 00:02:33,358
and earlier, will have
their statute of limitations

28
00:02:33,424 --> 00:02:34,926
considered expired,

29
00:02:34,993 --> 00:02:38,963
while cases from the 28th will have
no statute and remain open.

30
00:02:39,964 --> 00:02:42,100
The amendment bill for the review…

31
00:02:50,174 --> 00:02:51,876
Only two days.

32
00:02:58,149 --> 00:02:59,651
It was just two days…

33
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,255
Now, we can't arrest them.

34
00:03:10,495 --> 00:03:17,168
2026

35
00:03:29,781 --> 00:03:31,416
RELAXED FARM: A COW-RAISING GAME

36
00:03:31,482 --> 00:03:33,217
OTHER RECOMMENDED APPS

37
00:03:37,655 --> 00:03:39,891
CONGRATULATIONS.
IT'S A HEALTHY BABY COW!

38
00:03:39,957 --> 00:03:42,794
SHIORI KUDO: PLEASE GET HERE ALREADY

39
00:03:52,837 --> 00:03:56,074
He always texted back,
he was nice, and we got along.

40
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:57,909
I thought he was perfect.

41
00:03:57,975 --> 00:03:59,143
-Yes.
-But…

42
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:00,812
Turns out he had a hidden side.

43
00:04:00,878 --> 00:04:02,146
A hidden side?

44
00:04:02,213 --> 00:04:05,583
I went to his house,
and I ran into his side piece!

45
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:08,619
She told me,
"Sorry. My boyfriend deceived you."

46
00:04:08,686 --> 00:04:10,855
-She was crying, making a scene.
-What?

47
00:04:10,922 --> 00:04:14,459
Anyway, I didn't get it, so I asked him,
"Which one of us are you dating?"

48
00:04:14,525 --> 00:04:16,828
-And what do you think he said?
-What?

49
00:04:17,328 --> 00:04:18,763
"Neither of you."

50
00:04:18,830 --> 00:04:19,664
What?

51
00:04:19,731 --> 00:04:24,202
Next, we have a coroner from the Kanagawa
Police Department, First Division.

52
00:04:24,268 --> 00:04:25,370
Inspector Tagusari.

53
00:04:25,436 --> 00:04:29,340
PARTICLES FOUND BETWEEN VICTIMS' NAILS

54
00:04:31,476 --> 00:04:34,212
FIRST INVESTIGATIVE DIVISION

55
00:04:37,014 --> 00:04:38,983
My name is Tagusari,
I'm a Medical Examiner.

56
00:04:39,684 --> 00:04:43,588
Regarding the small particles
detected under the victims' nails,

57
00:04:44,188 --> 00:04:47,892
we've limited their possible origins
to a few factories in Kanagawa.

58
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:51,262
Just to be safe, I have expanded
the search to the Kanto suburbs,

59
00:04:51,329 --> 00:04:53,264
and the list of factories is attached.

60
00:04:53,331 --> 00:04:56,567
Then, the closet suddenly
clicked open, and someone came out.

61
00:04:57,068 --> 00:04:57,902
Who came out?

62
00:04:57,969 --> 00:04:59,570
A girl from my work!

63
00:04:59,637 --> 00:05:00,638
What?

64
00:05:00,705 --> 00:05:02,940
They got friendly while I wasn't looking.

65
00:05:03,641 --> 00:05:05,143
MAKOTO TAGUSARI: I'M ON MY WAY

66
00:05:05,209 --> 00:05:07,245
SHIORI KUDO: WHEN WILL YOU ARRIVE?

67
00:05:07,311 --> 00:05:08,813
MAKOTO TAGUSARI: SOON

68
00:05:14,419 --> 00:05:15,787
Mr. Tagusari.

69
00:05:16,421 --> 00:05:18,689
You don't plan on coming at all, huh?

70
00:05:19,857 --> 00:05:22,827
We got a request for support
from the Section Chief!

71
00:05:23,961 --> 00:05:24,796
No…

72
00:05:24,862 --> 00:05:26,697
I was just about to go.

73
00:05:26,764 --> 00:05:27,932
Then let's hurry.

74
00:05:32,236 --> 00:05:34,305
Oh, hello.

75
00:05:34,372 --> 00:05:35,306
Hello.

76
00:05:35,373 --> 00:05:38,843
The Director was happy.
He said you did great.

77
00:05:39,444 --> 00:05:42,180
He would like to have a meal with you
once the case is resolved.

78
00:05:42,246 --> 00:05:44,916
-Decline for me. Make up an excuse.
-Really?

79
00:05:45,783 --> 00:05:46,851
Tagusari.

80
00:05:48,453 --> 00:05:50,254
An unnatural death in Kanagawa Ward.

81
00:05:51,055 --> 00:05:52,223
Understood.

82
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:53,858
Okay.

83
00:06:05,136 --> 00:06:06,604
At around 7 a.m. today,

84
00:06:06,671 --> 00:06:09,841
when Ms. Nagisa Kuroki,
who works for a travel agency, got home,

85
00:06:09,907 --> 00:06:13,177
she found the man she was living with
dead from multiple injuries.

86
00:06:14,312 --> 00:06:18,916
The body was identified from his ID card
as Satoshi Makimura, 27 years old.

87
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:20,852
A part-timer at a restaurant--

88
00:06:20,918 --> 00:06:22,620
The entrance was locked?

89
00:06:23,354 --> 00:06:27,091
It seems only Ms. Kuroki
and Mr. Makimura had keys.

90
00:06:27,992 --> 00:06:30,194
Probably some lovers' spat. Here.

91
00:06:31,395 --> 00:06:34,432
But Mr. Tagusari,
she couldn't have done it.

92
00:06:34,499 --> 00:06:35,900
For the past week,

93
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:38,903
she was in Paris as a tour conductor
for an overseas tour.

94
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:44,041
Paris?

95
00:06:44,876 --> 00:06:48,212
If this was a murder,
it would be a locked-room mystery.

96
00:06:50,114 --> 00:06:51,148
What?

97
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,652
Spare me the convoluted tricks…

98
00:06:54,719 --> 00:06:56,320
Thank you.

99
00:06:57,588 --> 00:06:58,756
Hello.

100
00:06:58,823 --> 00:07:00,157
Hello.

101
00:07:00,224 --> 00:07:02,593
There are no signs
of entry from the balcony.

102
00:07:02,660 --> 00:07:04,362
What about a duplicate key?

103
00:07:04,428 --> 00:07:07,365
No suspicious persons seen
on the apartment security cameras.

104
00:07:07,431 --> 00:07:08,866
It's probably natural causes.

105
00:07:11,435 --> 00:07:13,070
Yeah. Like heart failure.

106
00:07:13,571 --> 00:07:16,007
How do you explain
the injuries on the body?

107
00:07:17,341 --> 00:07:20,211
For now, let's ask the coroner's opinion.

108
00:07:20,278 --> 00:07:23,281
-Okay.
-Oh, hello!

109
00:07:23,347 --> 00:07:24,315
Hello.

110
00:07:24,382 --> 00:07:26,651
I'm Kiritani
from the Medical Examiner's Office.

111
00:07:26,717 --> 00:07:29,587
Thank you for your help
in preserving the scene.

112
00:07:29,654 --> 00:07:31,789
Medical Examiner Tagusari has arrived.

113
00:07:31,856 --> 00:07:32,924
Go ahead.

114
00:07:45,369 --> 00:07:47,071
-I'll begin.
-Okay.

115
00:07:54,745 --> 00:07:56,347
Left temporal area.

116
00:07:56,414 --> 00:07:57,315
Okay.

117
00:08:01,118 --> 00:08:03,487
Left hand palm, an abrasion.

118
00:08:03,554 --> 00:08:04,655
Yes.

119
00:08:10,227 --> 00:08:11,696
None on the right.

120
00:08:11,762 --> 00:08:12,663
Yes.

121
00:08:18,302 --> 00:08:20,104
Left lumbar area, also an abrasion.

122
00:08:20,171 --> 00:08:21,038
Yes.

123
00:08:23,741 --> 00:08:25,476
Left abdomen…

124
00:08:26,644 --> 00:08:27,612
Discoloration?

125
00:08:28,212 --> 00:08:29,046
Okay.

126
00:08:33,584 --> 00:08:35,052
How long has it been?

127
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:37,221
Three weeks since you joined us…

128
00:08:37,855 --> 00:08:39,323
Getting used to the job yet?

129
00:08:41,993 --> 00:08:44,762
If you have any problems,
don't hesitate to speak up.

130
00:08:46,197 --> 00:08:48,499
The one having problems is me.

131
00:08:50,267 --> 00:08:52,770
At least be on time.

132
00:08:52,837 --> 00:08:53,704
What?

133
00:08:54,205 --> 00:08:56,307
You'll ruin my reputation too.

134
00:08:57,775 --> 00:09:00,344
Ishizaka, I'm on time, right?

135
00:09:01,946 --> 00:09:03,748
-I think you're fine.
-See?

136
00:09:05,316 --> 00:09:06,250
What?

137
00:09:06,317 --> 00:09:07,485
What is it?

138
00:09:07,551 --> 00:09:09,754
Sorry to keep you waiting.

139
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:11,255
What's the cause of death?

140
00:09:11,322 --> 00:09:12,990
Oh, I don't know yet.

141
00:09:13,057 --> 00:09:15,192
Is it related to the injuries?

142
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,228
I can't say for sure right now.

143
00:09:17,795 --> 00:09:18,896
Any information?

144
00:09:20,431 --> 00:09:23,968
As an Inspector, you must be making
good money. Make yourself useful.

145
00:09:25,536 --> 00:09:29,507
Estimated time of death is between
3:00 p.m. and 6:00 p.m. yesterday.

146
00:09:31,909 --> 00:09:33,044
Is that it?

147
00:09:35,413 --> 00:09:38,716
Is there anything else
that can be identified at this stage?

148
00:09:38,783 --> 00:09:39,550
No.

149
00:09:40,117 --> 00:09:42,586
Please proceed
with the autopsy procedures.

150
00:09:43,287 --> 00:09:44,188
Okay!

151
00:09:46,724 --> 00:09:48,426
MATSUIZUMI MEDICAL UNIVERSITY

152
00:10:00,971 --> 00:10:04,041
No rib fractures.

153
00:10:04,742 --> 00:10:07,945
Diaphragm, left fifth rib,
right fourth intercostal space,

154
00:10:08,012 --> 00:10:09,547
opening the chest.

155
00:10:09,613 --> 00:10:11,282
-Rib shears.
-Here.

156
00:10:16,253 --> 00:10:18,189
-Take a picture.
-Please look properly.

157
00:10:18,255 --> 00:10:19,090
I am looking.

158
00:10:20,024 --> 00:10:21,625
-Your eyes are closed.
-I'm looking!

159
00:10:21,692 --> 00:10:25,029
No fluid around the left and right lungs.

160
00:10:25,096 --> 00:10:26,430
Fluid in the lungs.

161
00:10:27,131 --> 00:10:29,200
Possibly caused by a heart attack?

162
00:10:29,266 --> 00:10:30,601
A heart attack…

163
00:10:31,102 --> 00:10:33,437
There was also cardiac hypertrophy.

164
00:10:33,504 --> 00:10:35,906
Perhaps heart failure
caused the buildup of fluids.

165
00:10:35,973 --> 00:10:36,907
Yoshida.

166
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:39,043
Mr. Kagura.

167
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:42,279
It's strange there's no
water buildup in the lungs.

168
00:10:42,847 --> 00:10:47,752
In that case, neurogenic pulmonary edema
is a possibility.

169
00:10:47,818 --> 00:10:49,520
If it's neurogenic,

170
00:10:50,521 --> 00:10:51,756
the fluid in the lungs

171
00:10:51,822 --> 00:10:55,259
might be caused by something
other than heart failure.

172
00:10:56,794 --> 00:11:00,331
The cause of the fluid buildup
was a head injury.

173
00:11:00,397 --> 00:11:02,700
This would be the fatal wound.

174
00:11:02,767 --> 00:11:05,102
Around when was the head injury sustained?

175
00:11:05,603 --> 00:11:08,038
The exact time is unknown. However…

176
00:11:08,105 --> 00:11:11,041
Since no fibroblast infiltration
was observed,

177
00:11:11,108 --> 00:11:13,177
it hasn't been 48 hours.

178
00:11:13,744 --> 00:11:16,213
-Estimated time of death?
-5:00 p.m. yesterday.

179
00:11:17,081 --> 00:11:20,751
In other words, the head injury
was sustained within 48 hours

180
00:11:20,818 --> 00:11:23,254
prior to 5:00 p.m. yesterday.

181
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,623
So the crime scene
may not be limited to that room.

182
00:11:27,358 --> 00:11:29,960
However, we don't know
if this injury was accidental

183
00:11:30,027 --> 00:11:32,129
or if there's foul play involved.

184
00:11:32,196 --> 00:11:34,298
Did he hit his head somewhere,

185
00:11:34,365 --> 00:11:36,534
or was he assaulted?

186
00:11:38,302 --> 00:11:40,070
I'll contact headquarters.

187
00:11:40,137 --> 00:11:43,340
Oh, tell them to check
Mr. Makimura's clothes.

188
00:11:43,407 --> 00:11:46,477
The clothes he wore when injured
should be at his home.

189
00:11:46,544 --> 00:11:47,711
Understood.

190
00:11:51,816 --> 00:11:53,617
Don't do anything unnecessary.

191
00:11:53,684 --> 00:11:56,954
-You're the one who told me to work.
-It's probably an accident.

192
00:11:57,021 --> 00:11:58,856
Investigating that is your job.

193
00:11:59,356 --> 00:12:01,826
I only care about knowing
the truth of how he died.

194
00:12:02,393 --> 00:12:03,561
Mr. Tagusari!

195
00:12:06,363 --> 00:12:08,999
I've got the post-mortem certificate.

196
00:12:13,571 --> 00:12:14,872
-Thank you.
-Yes.

197
00:12:16,307 --> 00:12:17,441
Here you go.

198
00:12:19,710 --> 00:12:21,345
My job is done here.

199
00:12:22,913 --> 00:12:24,181
Inspector Tagusari.

200
00:12:28,419 --> 00:12:29,720
Lend me some money.

201
00:12:30,387 --> 00:12:32,523
-There's a big race coming up.
-Quit it…

202
00:12:34,391 --> 00:12:35,626
Excuse me.

203
00:13:10,694 --> 00:13:11,528
Here.

204
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:14,632
Oh, wow.

205
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:17,668
Hey…

206
00:13:17,735 --> 00:13:19,236
This shop is…

207
00:13:20,337 --> 00:13:21,438
Health certificate.

208
00:13:21,505 --> 00:13:22,606
Right, yes.

209
00:13:28,178 --> 00:13:29,580
Well…

210
00:13:29,647 --> 00:13:33,350
Your eGFR is, well, just barely okay.

211
00:13:34,084 --> 00:13:35,119
Oh, right…

212
00:13:35,185 --> 00:13:38,555
About how much for one kidney…

213
00:13:38,622 --> 00:13:39,657
It hurts!

214
00:13:39,723 --> 00:13:41,425
Old man, go to work.

215
00:13:41,492 --> 00:13:42,693
Oh, gosh.

216
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,028
The certificate.

217
00:13:46,864 --> 00:13:48,232
Oh, it hurts…

218
00:13:48,732 --> 00:13:50,567
It hurts.

219
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:59,143
-You're interfering with my business.
-What is this?

220
00:13:59,643 --> 00:14:01,612
Just be quick about it.

221
00:14:01,679 --> 00:14:03,247
We don't buy this here.

222
00:14:04,815 --> 00:14:05,649
What?

223
00:14:05,716 --> 00:14:06,483
Huh?

224
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:09,386
I gave you this as a gift
when you first got the job!

225
00:14:10,955 --> 00:14:12,489
I'll buy it back once I win the race.

226
00:14:13,524 --> 00:14:14,425
You're terrible.

227
00:14:14,491 --> 00:14:15,359
Hey…

228
00:14:25,069 --> 00:14:26,837
Just take this and go home.

229
00:14:28,973 --> 00:14:29,974
Haruko.

230
00:14:30,474 --> 00:14:33,777
I can't buy a betting ticket
with dumplings, you know.

231
00:14:34,278 --> 00:14:35,713
They're not for you.

232
00:14:35,779 --> 00:14:37,348
They're a gift for Minoru.

233
00:14:38,248 --> 00:14:41,819
Unlike his tactless older brother,
he's actually well put-together.

234
00:14:55,966 --> 00:15:02,306
COVO REVERIO AOI

235
00:15:11,015 --> 00:15:12,583
I'm home.

236
00:15:12,649 --> 00:15:13,650
Welcome back.

237
00:15:17,254 --> 00:15:18,322
From Haruko.

238
00:15:18,989 --> 00:15:19,890
Okay.

239
00:15:29,066 --> 00:15:31,602
You're not planning
to crash here indefinitely?

240
00:15:34,138 --> 00:15:35,506
FUREASU APARTMENTS

241
00:15:35,572 --> 00:15:37,908
This place is close to my work.

242
00:15:37,975 --> 00:15:39,109
Makoto.

243
00:15:39,176 --> 00:15:41,445
I'll leave if you get
a girlfriend or something.

244
00:15:41,945 --> 00:15:43,180
Not in this lifetime then.

245
00:15:43,247 --> 00:15:45,182
Only because you aren't serious about it!

246
00:15:47,418 --> 00:15:48,285
Oh, wait.

247
00:15:48,352 --> 00:15:49,553
Wash up first!

248
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:50,454
What?

249
00:15:50,521 --> 00:15:52,256
You were at an autopsy.

250
00:16:12,242 --> 00:16:13,377
Makoto.

251
00:16:14,511 --> 00:16:16,513
The body we found today…

252
00:16:17,247 --> 00:16:19,516
Don't bring it home. Stop.

253
00:16:20,651 --> 00:16:24,021
That body had an abrasion on the palm.

254
00:16:24,521 --> 00:16:27,357
Normally, if you fall,
you instinctively put your hands out.

255
00:16:28,792 --> 00:16:33,030
If you had no time to put them out,
the damage should be more severe.

256
00:16:33,797 --> 00:16:36,700
Under what circumstances
did he get those injuries?

257
00:16:37,501 --> 00:16:38,969
Why didn't you say this earlier?

258
00:16:40,838 --> 00:16:42,239
It's just a guess.

259
00:16:42,306 --> 00:16:44,274
Aren't investigations all guesswork?

260
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,678
What if I guessed wrong?

261
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:53,383
I've been tossed around plenty
by relying on guesses.

262
00:16:56,053 --> 00:16:58,355
I'm only interested in the truth.

263
00:17:07,331 --> 00:17:09,099
I've heard that a million times.

264
00:17:19,910 --> 00:17:20,978
Ten.

265
00:17:21,044 --> 00:17:22,112
Nine.

266
00:17:22,179 --> 00:17:23,013
Eight.

267
00:17:23,580 --> 00:17:24,648
-Seven.
-Hey…

268
00:17:24,715 --> 00:17:25,749
Six.

269
00:17:25,816 --> 00:17:27,017
-Five.
-Morning.

270
00:17:27,084 --> 00:17:28,385
-Four.
-Morning.

271
00:17:28,452 --> 00:17:29,453
Three.

272
00:17:29,953 --> 00:17:30,854
Two.

273
00:17:30,921 --> 00:17:34,224
Well, it's true that you are on time.

274
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:36,260
He's almost late every time. Not good.

275
00:17:36,326 --> 00:17:39,296
Will my coming five minutes early
increase the arrest rate?

276
00:17:39,363 --> 00:17:41,899
It makes a huge difference
in our initial response.

277
00:17:42,466 --> 00:17:43,800
What a pain.

278
00:17:44,601 --> 00:17:46,203
Are you two at it again?

279
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:47,905
Morning.

280
00:17:47,971 --> 00:17:50,374
I guess having vitality is a good thing.

281
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:53,076
It would be great if that vitality
caught criminals too.

282
00:17:53,143 --> 00:17:55,913
But this time, we don't even know
if there is a criminal.

283
00:17:56,446 --> 00:17:59,149
I'll go to Mr. Makimura's
part-time job to trace his steps.

284
00:17:59,216 --> 00:17:59,917
Please do.

285
00:17:59,983 --> 00:18:01,618
We'll investigate his girlfriend.

286
00:18:01,685 --> 00:18:04,254
Where in those 48 hours
did he sustain the head injury?

287
00:18:04,321 --> 00:18:06,423
Consider both accident and foul play.

288
00:18:06,490 --> 00:18:07,824
-Yes.
-We will.

289
00:18:12,296 --> 00:18:15,065
If he was assaulted,
we'll have to set up a task force.

290
00:18:15,632 --> 00:18:17,668
A joint investigation with First Division.

291
00:18:20,537 --> 00:18:23,240
Please let it be an accident. Please…

292
00:18:23,307 --> 00:18:24,675
Hello.

293
00:18:25,209 --> 00:18:27,578
Mr. Makimura's family has arrived.

294
00:18:27,644 --> 00:18:30,180
I explained the autopsy process
to the family.

295
00:18:30,247 --> 00:18:31,081
Kudo.

296
00:18:32,749 --> 00:18:33,717
Tagusari.

297
00:18:40,324 --> 00:18:42,125
Hurry along.

298
00:18:42,826 --> 00:18:44,294
Yes, okay.

299
00:18:46,763 --> 00:18:48,031
Such a pain.

300
00:18:55,405 --> 00:18:57,641
Is he your family member?

301
00:18:59,109 --> 00:19:01,878
We'll now begin the procedures
for releasing his body…

302
00:19:01,945 --> 00:19:02,846
Wait…

303
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:04,514
Is something wrong?

304
00:19:05,983 --> 00:19:07,417
Isn't he your son?

305
00:19:07,985 --> 00:19:09,152
No.

306
00:19:09,219 --> 00:19:10,954
This isn't Satoshi.

307
00:19:11,688 --> 00:19:15,125
Please take a good look.
Perhaps he's thinner than before?

308
00:19:15,192 --> 00:19:17,394
My son is already over 40.

309
00:19:17,461 --> 00:19:19,696
He can't be young like this.

310
00:19:31,241 --> 00:19:33,910
He was using an ID card
to fake his identity.

311
00:19:33,977 --> 00:19:35,345
Do we have his fingerprints?

312
00:19:35,412 --> 00:19:36,580
He was never arrested.

313
00:19:36,647 --> 00:19:39,082
He probably ran away
after getting into debt.

314
00:19:40,851 --> 00:19:42,219
Oh, hello.

315
00:19:42,286 --> 00:19:43,453
Hello.

316
00:19:43,987 --> 00:19:47,291
Mr. Makimura wasn't on shift
at his part-time job during that time.

317
00:19:47,991 --> 00:19:51,061
Then, his whereabouts
during those 48 hours…

318
00:19:51,762 --> 00:19:53,830
I'll check his social circle,

319
00:19:53,897 --> 00:19:56,266
but I hope we get something
from his girlfriend.

320
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:57,968
Oh, right.

321
00:19:58,035 --> 00:20:00,337
The jacket Mr. Makimura often wore,

322
00:20:00,404 --> 00:20:03,073
I found it in the footage
from the CCTV at his workplace.

323
00:20:05,375 --> 00:20:07,311
Well, our body isn't Makimura, though.

324
00:20:10,414 --> 00:20:11,682
This body…

325
00:20:11,748 --> 00:20:14,084
Now we know even less about it.

326
00:20:14,651 --> 00:20:18,855
Where, how, why it happened,
as well as who he is.

327
00:20:18,922 --> 00:20:21,091
Now I wish
it was just a locked-room trick.

328
00:20:21,658 --> 00:20:24,161
For now,
let's clear things up, one by one.

329
00:20:24,227 --> 00:20:26,463
His girlfriend might know something.

330
00:20:28,131 --> 00:20:30,467
-Can I drop you off at HQ?
-Yes, please.

331
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:41,411
I'll be home late today.

332
00:20:43,213 --> 00:20:44,381
You won't need dinner?

333
00:20:44,948 --> 00:20:46,350
Yes, you eat first.

334
00:20:48,118 --> 00:20:51,254
But I'm also busy
with examinations this afternoon.

335
00:20:51,321 --> 00:20:53,223
Maybe I'll just whip up some beef bowls.

336
00:20:55,726 --> 00:20:56,827
Beef bowls, huh.

337
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:03,033
LET'S GIVE THEM A NAME

338
00:21:04,735 --> 00:21:06,770
Maybe I'll eat out today.

339
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:11,608
I'll get off here.

340
00:21:11,675 --> 00:21:13,110
Thank you very much.

341
00:21:13,176 --> 00:21:14,411
Goodbye.

342
00:21:21,284 --> 00:21:25,555
You two seem more like
a married couple than brothers.

343
00:21:41,405 --> 00:21:42,706
Excuse me.

344
00:21:42,773 --> 00:21:44,875
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

345
00:21:46,209 --> 00:21:47,544
You didn't know?

346
00:21:48,044 --> 00:21:51,081
I started dating him two years ago.

347
00:21:51,148 --> 00:21:54,284
At that time, he said
his name was Satoshi Makimura.

348
00:21:54,885 --> 00:21:57,020
What about before you started dating?

349
00:21:57,687 --> 00:22:00,023
It seems he had several part-time jobs.

350
00:22:01,491 --> 00:22:04,094
Do you know anything about those jobs?

351
00:22:04,161 --> 00:22:08,365
Or anything about his hometown,
family, or background?

352
00:22:08,432 --> 00:22:09,466
I don't.

353
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:11,802
Suddenly asking me about his past…

354
00:22:11,868 --> 00:22:13,170
I don't even know anymore.

355
00:22:17,641 --> 00:22:18,842
In the end,

356
00:22:20,644 --> 00:22:22,646
I didn't know anything, did I?

357
00:22:25,048 --> 00:22:26,550
Not even his name.

358
00:22:27,717 --> 00:22:30,554
To think I don't even know why he died.

359
00:22:47,838 --> 00:22:49,473
Do you know what he did those two days?

360
00:22:50,106 --> 00:22:53,109
When I'm working,
I hardly ever contact him.

361
00:22:54,311 --> 00:22:56,513
Excuse me. May we borrow that jacket?

362
00:22:57,848 --> 00:22:58,982
Sure.

363
00:23:12,262 --> 00:23:13,497
Send this to forensics.

364
00:23:13,997 --> 00:23:14,898
Yes.

365
00:23:19,769 --> 00:23:22,739
Did you notice
anything different about him lately?

366
00:23:28,345 --> 00:23:29,613
Even a guess is fine.

367
00:23:30,947 --> 00:23:31,948
Just tell me.

368
00:23:35,619 --> 00:23:37,354
I noticed it this morning.

369
00:23:37,954 --> 00:23:41,825
He always used to leave his bicycle here.

370
00:23:42,559 --> 00:23:45,095
Was it gone by the time
you returned to Japan?

371
00:23:46,363 --> 00:23:47,864
Did he use it often?

372
00:23:48,665 --> 00:23:52,636
It's a bit of a distance to the station,
so when he took the train, he'd ride it.

373
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,615
The palms don't touch it.

374
00:24:07,384 --> 00:24:10,720
Between the house and the station,
we found Mr. Makimura… Oh.

375
00:24:11,521 --> 00:24:14,324
I mean, the former Mr. Makimura's bike.

376
00:24:15,792 --> 00:24:18,962
The rear wheel is deformed,
so it's likely an accident.

377
00:24:19,596 --> 00:24:21,498
Yes. Excuse me.

378
00:24:22,899 --> 00:24:24,367
A hit-and-run, huh?

379
00:24:25,035 --> 00:24:27,137
He didn't report it to the police.

380
00:24:27,871 --> 00:24:30,774
He couldn't, right?
Because he was hiding his identity.

381
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,409
Oh, that’s true.

382
00:24:34,377 --> 00:24:36,680
Our case was a hit-and-run,

383
00:24:36,746 --> 00:24:39,816
so we’ll leave the rest to you,
the Traffic Department.

384
00:24:39,883 --> 00:24:40,817
Yes.

385
00:24:40,884 --> 00:24:43,053
Oh, it’s finally over.

386
00:24:43,119 --> 00:24:44,087
Tagusari!

387
00:24:44,854 --> 00:24:46,056
I’m sorry.

388
00:24:46,122 --> 00:24:48,592
We’re a bit short-staffed.
Could you give us a hand?

389
00:24:48,658 --> 00:24:49,693
What?

390
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:53,930
We got a tip-off,
and are currently pursuing this guy.

391
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:59,235
It would be great
if the Violent Crimes Division

392
00:24:59,302 --> 00:25:02,205
could search for the car
that hit our former Mr. Makimura.

393
00:25:02,806 --> 00:25:05,041
HIT AND RUN CASE

394
00:25:05,108 --> 00:25:08,945
THE STATUTE IS ALMOST UP!
REQUESTING INFORMATION TO AID ARREST!

395
00:25:24,060 --> 00:25:26,696
CHINESE RESTAURANT
MOCCHAN

396
00:25:26,763 --> 00:25:27,864
-Huh?
-What?

397
00:25:27,931 --> 00:25:28,999
It's closed.

398
00:25:30,533 --> 00:25:31,401
Huh?

399
00:25:32,969 --> 00:25:33,903
Let's just open it.

400
00:25:34,871 --> 00:25:36,606
Heave-ho.

401
00:25:38,608 --> 00:25:39,643
Mogi?

402
00:25:41,578 --> 00:25:43,346
Is he out getting ingredients?

403
00:25:43,413 --> 00:25:44,814
Maybe…

404
00:25:44,881 --> 00:25:46,149
Shall we start first?

405
00:25:46,216 --> 00:25:47,384
Okay.

406
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:48,685
Go get the snacks.

407
00:25:48,752 --> 00:25:49,986
Got it.

408
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,938
And here I thought the case was over.

409
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:12,275
You seem really fed up with that body.

410
00:26:12,342 --> 00:26:13,209
Shut up.

411
00:26:13,276 --> 00:26:16,179
Once the car model is identified,
are you chasing the car next?

412
00:26:18,882 --> 00:26:20,817
I wish they'd just turn themselves in.

413
00:26:23,753 --> 00:26:25,321
What are you guys doing?

414
00:26:27,257 --> 00:26:29,592
Don't talk about cases
in a place like this.

415
00:26:30,794 --> 00:26:31,828
There are no customers.

416
00:26:31,895 --> 00:26:33,463
I overheard a little bit.

417
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:34,798
You're fine, Mogi.

418
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:37,500
More importantly, lock the door.
I told you before.

419
00:26:37,567 --> 00:26:38,601
Oh, sorry.

420
00:26:38,668 --> 00:26:40,904
I was thinking about
what to buy and forgot…

421
00:26:40,970 --> 00:26:42,472
-Mogi, yakisoba.
-Me too.

422
00:26:42,539 --> 00:26:43,373
Coming up.

423
00:26:46,843 --> 00:26:47,944
Let me through.

424
00:26:57,854 --> 00:26:59,089
Did something happen?

425
00:26:59,689 --> 00:27:00,523
What?

426
00:27:01,124 --> 00:27:03,727
It's rare for you to help
another department out.

427
00:27:07,297 --> 00:27:10,233
The Traffic Department's suspect
was also a hit-and-run.

428
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:13,503
He has been on the run for 20 years
after causing a fatal accident.

429
00:27:19,109 --> 00:27:20,877
The statute of limitations is almost up.

430
00:27:24,781 --> 00:27:26,149
I see.

431
00:27:35,391 --> 00:27:39,062
1995, APRIL 26

432
00:27:39,129 --> 00:27:41,364
You have to make the noodles
"swim" around a bit.

433
00:27:41,431 --> 00:27:43,166
-Swim?
-Yes.

434
00:27:44,167 --> 00:27:45,068
That's it.

435
00:27:45,135 --> 00:27:47,003
-I think it’s good.
-Is it?

436
00:27:51,708 --> 00:27:54,043
So dinner is yakisoba.

437
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:56,012
Mom is so bad at making it.

438
00:27:56,079 --> 00:27:59,282
-I wonder if she has been practicing.
-It's really not yum--

439
00:27:59,349 --> 00:28:00,216
Hey!

440
00:28:01,117 --> 00:28:02,752
I can hear you!

441
00:28:02,819 --> 00:28:04,020
Oh, no!

442
00:28:32,048 --> 00:28:34,184
Mr. Tagusari, do you have a moment?

443
00:28:34,717 --> 00:28:36,886
You again? So persistent.

444
00:28:36,953 --> 00:28:40,123
Without your witness testimony,
the proposal won't get approved.

445
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:41,791
I don't care about that!

446
00:28:41,858 --> 00:28:42,926
Mr. Tagusari.

447
00:28:42,992 --> 00:28:45,028
You were smuggling, weren't you?

448
00:28:45,094 --> 00:28:46,896
From offshore.

449
00:28:46,963 --> 00:28:47,797
Tell us.

450
00:28:47,864 --> 00:28:49,232
I have nothing to say.

451
00:28:50,133 --> 00:28:53,069
Mr. Tagusari, you transported
goods to the port too, right?

452
00:28:54,070 --> 00:28:55,038
Hey.

453
00:28:55,104 --> 00:28:56,739
Let me hear your side. Hey!

454
00:28:56,806 --> 00:28:58,608
-I'm busy, go home.
-No!

455
00:28:59,175 --> 00:29:01,811
I'll come by again tonight.

456
00:29:01,878 --> 00:29:03,479
Here goes…

457
00:29:06,516 --> 00:29:10,553
-What? We'll have dinner soon, you know.
-Who said they were going to quit smoking?

458
00:29:11,154 --> 00:29:13,356
No… Me, smoking?

459
00:29:13,423 --> 00:29:16,092
I can tell by the smell.

460
00:29:16,159 --> 00:29:18,194
Stinky.

461
00:29:18,261 --> 00:29:20,864
Dad! Who were you talking to
outside just now?

462
00:29:20,930 --> 00:29:21,764
What?

463
00:29:22,732 --> 00:29:25,535
Apparently, your dad will be interviewed.

464
00:29:25,602 --> 00:29:26,469
An interview?

465
00:29:26,536 --> 00:29:27,704
You'll be on TV?

466
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:29,639
-Don't be stupid!
-Will you get money?

467
00:29:29,706 --> 00:29:31,608
-What?
-Buy me a PS1!

468
00:29:31,674 --> 00:29:33,009
-No…
-I want a picture book!

469
00:29:33,076 --> 00:29:34,744
I told you, that’s not it.

470
00:29:34,811 --> 00:29:36,346
Look, it's time to eat.

471
00:29:36,412 --> 00:29:37,280
Let’s eat.

472
00:29:37,347 --> 00:29:38,414
Here you go.

473
00:29:39,816 --> 00:29:41,384
You're using that again?

474
00:29:41,451 --> 00:29:42,518
What?

475
00:29:42,585 --> 00:29:44,320
It's delicious!

476
00:29:44,387 --> 00:29:45,722
You guys want to try some?

477
00:29:45,788 --> 00:29:46,656
No!

478
00:29:46,723 --> 00:29:49,292
-Let me put it on for you! Hey!
-No!

479
00:29:49,359 --> 00:29:51,194
-Please don't!
-Come on, it's good.

480
00:29:51,261 --> 00:29:52,629
It's yummy, you know.

481
00:29:52,695 --> 00:29:53,596
Okay, let’s eat!

482
00:29:53,663 --> 00:29:54,564
Let's eat.

483
00:29:54,631 --> 00:29:56,065
Looks good.

484
00:29:58,368 --> 00:29:59,702
I poured on too much.

485
00:30:00,336 --> 00:30:01,170
Yummy.

486
00:30:37,140 --> 00:30:38,641
It hurts!

487
00:30:38,708 --> 00:30:40,276
-Minoru!
-It hurts!

488
00:30:40,343 --> 00:30:41,978
-Minoru?
-It hurts!

489
00:30:42,045 --> 00:30:43,646
It hurts!

490
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:45,648
It hurts!

491
00:30:46,316 --> 00:30:47,817
It hurts!

492
00:30:47,884 --> 00:30:48,952
Mom! Dad!

493
00:30:49,018 --> 00:30:49,919
-It hurts!
-Minoru's…

494
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:51,754
It hurts!

495
00:30:52,755 --> 00:30:54,190
It hurts…

496
00:30:55,325 --> 00:30:56,960
It hurts…

497
00:31:09,138 --> 00:31:10,506
Makoto!

498
00:31:10,573 --> 00:31:12,308
It hurts…

499
00:31:12,375 --> 00:31:13,576
It hurts!

500
00:31:14,277 --> 00:31:16,079
It hurts!

501
00:31:16,145 --> 00:31:19,282
Around 11:00 p.m.
on the 26th of last month,

502
00:31:19,349 --> 00:31:22,518
at a residence in Yomogida-cho,
Kawasaki Ward, Kawasaki City,

503
00:31:22,585 --> 00:31:28,324
residents Mr. Sakutaro Tagusari,
and his wife, Yuka, were found murdered.

504
00:31:28,891 --> 00:31:31,394
The perpetrator
has not yet been identified.

505
00:31:32,395 --> 00:31:36,532
Sakutaro and Yuka were killed
by stabs to the chest and shoulders.

506
00:31:36,599 --> 00:31:39,402
Based on the condition of the bodies,
the weapon used was…

507
00:31:40,269 --> 00:31:41,504
Here you go, yakisoba.

508
00:31:42,138 --> 00:31:43,139
Thanks.

509
00:32:18,608 --> 00:32:19,742
I still don't get it.

510
00:32:24,781 --> 00:32:26,149
It’s just sour.

511
00:32:31,220 --> 00:32:33,589
Is the former Makimura's girlfriend okay?

512
00:32:34,857 --> 00:32:35,792
No.

513
00:32:38,694 --> 00:32:41,431
Please find the killer, for her.

514
00:32:43,766 --> 00:32:47,036
Because for the people left behind,
time just stops.

515
00:33:00,149 --> 00:33:01,017
Hey.

516
00:33:07,957 --> 00:33:09,459
These are all fakes anyway.

517
00:33:10,359 --> 00:33:11,527
How rude.

518
00:33:11,594 --> 00:33:13,396
I have the real ones somewhere.

519
00:33:14,430 --> 00:33:15,631
That's great.

520
00:33:19,802 --> 00:33:22,038
So, what do you need today?

521
00:33:22,738 --> 00:33:25,141
I can't lend you money
in exchange for dumplings.

522
00:33:31,314 --> 00:33:32,615
Find his identity.

523
00:33:33,116 --> 00:33:36,552
-This is a pawnshop.
-Before this, you were a reporter, no?

524
00:33:38,387 --> 00:33:39,755
What did this man do?

525
00:33:42,725 --> 00:33:44,460
He died in a hit-and-run.

526
00:33:45,361 --> 00:33:46,529
Can I count on you?

527
00:33:48,097 --> 00:33:51,234
What? Have you decided
to become a detective for justice?

528
00:33:52,568 --> 00:33:55,138
If justice existed,
I'd sell it to you for one yen.

529
00:34:06,249 --> 00:34:07,450
What do you want?

530
00:34:07,950 --> 00:34:09,085
Hello?

531
00:34:10,119 --> 00:34:12,855
I'm looking for someone.
Could you look into it?

532
00:34:18,761 --> 00:34:20,062
From the bicycle's paint,

533
00:34:20,129 --> 00:34:24,567
we found that the car that hit
the so-called Makimura was a white van.

534
00:34:27,336 --> 00:34:30,873
However, after checking surveillance
cameras on Hayase Street…

535
00:34:31,807 --> 00:34:32,975
What, 104 cars?

536
00:34:33,809 --> 00:34:35,177
It's quite a common car model.

537
00:34:37,313 --> 00:34:38,814
Well, makes sense.

538
00:34:38,881 --> 00:34:42,985
Over a span of 48 hours, there should be
that many cars that took that road.

539
00:34:43,052 --> 00:34:47,990
But if we have to check 104 cars,
I don't know how many days it will take.

540
00:34:48,057 --> 00:34:50,493
This should be handled
by Traffic Department,

541
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:52,995
but we are tied up with another case.

542
00:34:54,497 --> 00:34:56,866
Please do what you can, within reason.

543
00:34:56,933 --> 00:34:57,934
Understood.

544
00:35:02,505 --> 00:35:05,241
The Traffic Department knows, doesn't it?

545
00:35:05,308 --> 00:35:08,711
It's not guaranteed that all the cars
are from Kanagawa.

546
00:35:08,778 --> 00:35:12,281
We have to check a few,
and hope we get lucky.

547
00:35:12,348 --> 00:35:15,151
104 cars…

548
00:35:15,885 --> 00:35:17,019
Seriously?

549
00:35:19,488 --> 00:35:21,357
We got through
just four cars this morning.

550
00:35:21,424 --> 00:35:23,326
This is quite tough.

551
00:35:36,172 --> 00:35:37,640
Go on ahead.

552
00:35:37,707 --> 00:35:39,976
Wait, you'll get off here?

553
00:35:48,517 --> 00:35:51,554
Excuse me, please help.
Thank you very much.

554
00:35:52,188 --> 00:35:53,122
Please help.

555
00:35:53,956 --> 00:35:54,957
Please help.

556
00:35:56,092 --> 00:35:57,426
Please help.

557
00:36:14,443 --> 00:36:15,378
Here's 350 yen…

558
00:36:15,444 --> 00:36:17,246
That's 200 yen too much, Mogi.

559
00:36:17,313 --> 00:36:18,147
Right.

560
00:36:18,214 --> 00:36:19,048
Here.

561
00:36:19,115 --> 00:36:20,383
Right, sorry.

562
00:36:20,449 --> 00:36:21,450
Thanks for the meal.

563
00:36:22,018 --> 00:36:23,085
Thanks.

564
00:36:41,037 --> 00:36:42,038
Not picking that up?

565
00:36:42,538 --> 00:36:43,372
No.

566
00:36:44,807 --> 00:36:45,775
It's the Director.

567
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:48,544
He wants to go for a meal
since the case is resolved.

568
00:36:48,611 --> 00:36:51,113
Is that so? It's a chance for a promotion.

569
00:36:51,180 --> 00:36:52,348
Maybe.

570
00:36:53,516 --> 00:36:54,917
Oh, last time,

571
00:36:55,551 --> 00:36:58,521
you prevented a terrorist attack,
so you got a special…

572
00:36:58,587 --> 00:37:00,056
Special promotion.

573
00:37:00,122 --> 00:37:00,956
Right!

574
00:37:01,023 --> 00:37:02,725
That’s how you became Inspector.

575
00:37:02,792 --> 00:37:04,026
Next is…

576
00:37:04,093 --> 00:37:05,661
I'm not really interested.

577
00:37:06,395 --> 00:37:07,730
Why not?

578
00:37:07,797 --> 00:37:09,231
What a waste!

579
00:37:09,799 --> 00:37:12,001
I didn't join the police for that.

580
00:37:12,668 --> 00:37:15,338
And besides,
I'm not good with living people,

581
00:37:15,404 --> 00:37:17,273
so my current position is just right.

582
00:37:23,145 --> 00:37:24,213
Not going to see Haruko?

583
00:37:29,385 --> 00:37:34,090
You finally found out
where she is, so go see her.

584
00:37:35,791 --> 00:37:38,427
To you guys,
she's like an older sister, isn't she?

585
00:37:45,634 --> 00:37:46,802
So persistent.

586
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:50,039
FORENSICS

587
00:37:50,106 --> 00:37:52,108
Twelve… Twelve?

588
00:37:52,174 --> 00:37:53,342
Twelve cars?

589
00:37:53,409 --> 00:37:55,211
That's the most we can check in one day.

590
00:37:55,277 --> 00:37:58,280
Guess we have to work hard
until we can hand it back to Traffic.

591
00:38:01,183 --> 00:38:03,386
Let's start checking
tomorrow morning again.

592
00:38:03,452 --> 00:38:04,687
I'm counting on you.

593
00:38:04,754 --> 00:38:05,955
Good work today.

594
00:38:06,021 --> 00:38:07,456
-Bye.
-See you.

595
00:38:11,093 --> 00:38:13,362
You're on duty the night shift today?

596
00:38:14,397 --> 00:38:15,598
See you tomorrow.

597
00:38:15,664 --> 00:38:17,500
-I'm heading out first.
-Bye.

598
00:38:17,566 --> 00:38:19,001
-Bye.
-See you.

599
00:38:32,581 --> 00:38:34,483
The next car is…

600
00:38:40,356 --> 00:38:41,624
Working hard, I see.

601
00:38:43,392 --> 00:38:44,827
Of course.

602
00:38:45,494 --> 00:38:46,796
Why are you here?

603
00:38:46,862 --> 00:38:49,331
Stains were found
on the former Makimura's clothes.

604
00:38:52,401 --> 00:38:53,702
Did you analyze them?

605
00:38:54,370 --> 00:38:57,473
They turned out to be
cast iron rust and some oil.

606
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:01,177
It's similar to what's found
on screwdrivers or bolts.

607
00:39:02,711 --> 00:39:04,480
So some kind of tool…

608
00:39:04,547 --> 00:39:05,448
ANALYSIS

609
00:39:05,514 --> 00:39:08,451
These stains are too big, though.

610
00:39:10,019 --> 00:39:12,688
Whatever caused them
must have been on Hayase Street,

611
00:39:12,755 --> 00:39:16,892
where the bicycle was found,
during the two days from April 17th.

612
00:39:20,930 --> 00:39:22,264
Traffic Department again?

613
00:39:27,536 --> 00:39:31,540
April 17th…

614
00:39:35,311 --> 00:39:37,646
APRIL 17, 2026

615
00:39:37,713 --> 00:39:39,181
This is it.

616
00:39:39,248 --> 00:39:41,317
It's a pulley
for hoisting heavy equipment.

617
00:39:41,383 --> 00:39:43,152
What's the date and time of recovery?

618
00:39:44,019 --> 00:39:47,189
April 17th, 11:14 p.m.

619
00:39:47,256 --> 00:39:49,124
Two days ago, lucky.

620
00:39:49,925 --> 00:39:52,361
The accident occurred sometime
within the 48 hours

621
00:39:52,428 --> 00:39:54,730
before the estimated
time of death at 5:00 p.m.

622
00:39:55,264 --> 00:39:56,098
In other words,

623
00:39:56,165 --> 00:39:59,201
the accident occurred
between 5:00 p.m. and 11:14 p.m.

624
00:39:59,268 --> 00:40:02,605
two days ago,
when the fallen object was recovered.

625
00:40:03,172 --> 00:40:04,673
That's about six hours.

626
00:40:04,740 --> 00:40:07,076
The search for the white van
will be much easier.

627
00:40:09,712 --> 00:40:10,613
Minoru!

628
00:40:10,679 --> 00:40:12,448
Finding the criminal isn't my job.

629
00:40:16,719 --> 00:40:18,988
Five, four, nine, one…

630
00:40:48,017 --> 00:40:49,585
Two, one…

631
00:40:54,156 --> 00:40:56,191
Not this one.

632
00:41:36,932 --> 00:41:37,800
Good morning.

633
00:41:37,866 --> 00:41:38,968
Good morning.

634
00:41:56,485 --> 00:41:57,853
Kudo speaking.

635
00:42:04,493 --> 00:42:07,630
Thanks to the part that fell off,
we narrowed it down to 31 cars.

636
00:42:09,965 --> 00:42:11,967
All the way to Tateyama in Chiba…

637
00:42:13,102 --> 00:42:15,137
Did you investigate these all night?

638
00:42:15,204 --> 00:42:16,605
There are nine cars left.

639
00:42:16,672 --> 00:42:18,707
The hit-and-run car is among these.

640
00:42:25,581 --> 00:42:26,448
No.

641
00:42:28,083 --> 00:42:29,184
It's seven cars.

642
00:42:29,251 --> 00:42:32,021
MINORU: BOTH MINAMI-KASHIWA
AND FUTAKOTAMAGAWA WERE DUDS

643
00:42:45,401 --> 00:42:48,537
MAKOTO: I KNEW YOU WOULD HELP

644
00:42:54,043 --> 00:42:55,110
Three cars left.

645
00:43:05,487 --> 00:43:06,722
This house?

646
00:43:13,829 --> 00:43:16,098
I'm Kudo from the Aoi Station.

647
00:43:16,165 --> 00:43:17,800
You are Masaya Nogami, right?

648
00:43:17,866 --> 00:43:19,101
Police?

649
00:43:20,002 --> 00:43:23,305
There was an accident
on Hayase Street on April 17th.

650
00:43:23,372 --> 00:43:26,408
May we see your car, Mr. Nogami?

651
00:43:28,777 --> 00:43:31,080
There was a male victim who passed away.

652
00:43:33,248 --> 00:43:34,850
Please open your garage.

653
00:43:35,451 --> 00:43:37,820
Sorry. I have to get to work.

654
00:43:37,886 --> 00:43:39,321
Hey…

655
00:43:39,388 --> 00:43:41,523
-What are you doing?
-Show me your car.

656
00:43:42,091 --> 00:43:43,992
We'll find out eventually. A hit-and-run?

657
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:46,662
No. I didn't run away.

658
00:43:46,729 --> 00:43:48,564
Then what happened?

659
00:43:52,501 --> 00:43:54,002
Dad, what's wrong?

660
00:43:55,337 --> 00:43:56,438
It's nothing.

661
00:43:56,505 --> 00:43:57,773
Go to your room.

662
00:43:59,374 --> 00:44:01,343
Let's talk outside.

663
00:44:07,049 --> 00:44:10,119
I never thought he would die.

664
00:44:24,600 --> 00:44:25,701
VICTORY

665
00:44:28,403 --> 00:44:29,071
Ow!

666
00:44:30,973 --> 00:44:33,709
After I gave him 20,000 yen
for the bicycle repair,

667
00:44:33,776 --> 00:44:36,044
he left immediately.

668
00:44:37,746 --> 00:44:41,450
The victim had reasons
to refuse the police or hospital,

669
00:44:41,950 --> 00:44:45,220
and you, Mr. Nogami,
thought it was just an unlucky accident.

670
00:44:46,054 --> 00:44:51,360
I tried to contact the police too,
but he really said he was okay.

671
00:44:52,494 --> 00:44:53,662
Even so…

672
00:44:54,563 --> 00:44:57,332
Even so, you're still guilty.

673
00:44:57,933 --> 00:45:01,136
You violated the Road Traffic Act
for not reporting an accident.

674
00:45:01,804 --> 00:45:02,738
And…

675
00:45:04,106 --> 00:45:06,275
negligent driving resulting in death.

676
00:45:11,847 --> 00:45:13,582
There's someone who wants to know.

677
00:45:20,422 --> 00:45:25,661
Why someone important to them had to die.

678
00:45:30,699 --> 00:45:32,601
I'll come again next month.

679
00:45:33,202 --> 00:45:34,102
Okay?

680
00:45:34,169 --> 00:45:37,272
1996

681
00:45:43,378 --> 00:45:45,681
When will you catch them?

682
00:45:46,715 --> 00:45:49,418
Why did my mom and dad die?

683
00:45:55,858 --> 00:45:57,626
When you don't know anything…

684
00:46:00,162 --> 00:46:01,930
The pain just never stops.

685
00:46:48,143 --> 00:46:49,878
What has gotten into you?

686
00:46:51,847 --> 00:46:54,349
Normally, you'd be complaining
about it being a pain.

687
00:47:00,956 --> 00:47:01,857
Hey.

688
00:47:01,924 --> 00:47:03,158
Where are you going?

689
00:47:03,225 --> 00:47:08,163
LOOKING FOR WITNESSES
OF A TRAFFIC ACCIDENT

690
00:47:17,306 --> 00:47:19,074
Please help.

691
00:47:20,876 --> 00:47:22,077
Excuse me, please help.

692
00:47:24,446 --> 00:47:25,380
Please help.

693
00:47:27,182 --> 00:47:28,383
Please help.

694
00:47:30,185 --> 00:47:31,420
Please help.

695
00:47:34,189 --> 00:47:35,190
Please help.

696
00:47:35,257 --> 00:47:37,693
I'm looking for someone
who witnessed this murder!

697
00:47:38,493 --> 00:47:40,862
It happened April 26th!

698
00:47:40,929 --> 00:47:42,965
I'm looking for someone
who witnessed this murder!

699
00:47:43,031 --> 00:47:45,701
It happened April 26th!

700
00:47:59,514 --> 00:48:00,482
Please help.

701
00:48:07,856 --> 00:48:08,790
That's enough.

702
00:48:17,265 --> 00:48:19,267
I can't give any details yet,

703
00:48:21,703 --> 00:48:24,272
but we have secured a suspect.

704
00:48:26,408 --> 00:48:27,275
Really?

705
00:48:33,715 --> 00:48:35,117
Thank you very much.

706
00:49:20,262 --> 00:49:22,397
The Diet has passed a bill today

707
00:49:22,464 --> 00:49:26,768
to abolish the statute of limitations
for heinous crimes, such as murder.

708
00:49:26,835 --> 00:49:30,572
And this evening, it was put
into effect with unusual speed.

709
00:49:30,639 --> 00:49:31,840
2010, APRIL 27

710
00:49:31,907 --> 00:49:35,777
Under this bill, crimes for which
the statute of limitations has expired

711
00:49:35,844 --> 00:49:38,847
cannot have this statute
retroactively abolished.

712
00:49:39,414 --> 00:49:41,383
As a result, cases from April 27, 2010,

713
00:49:41,450 --> 00:49:43,952
and earlier, will have
their statute of limitations

714
00:49:44,019 --> 00:49:45,387
considered expired,

715
00:49:45,987 --> 00:49:49,925
while cases from the 28th will have
no statute and remain open.

716
00:49:50,625 --> 00:49:52,961
The amendment bill for the review…

717
00:50:00,602 --> 00:50:02,170
Only two days.

718
00:50:13,348 --> 00:50:14,749
It was just two days…

719
00:50:17,819 --> 00:50:19,754
Now, we can't arrest them.

720
00:50:27,662 --> 00:50:29,231
I couldn't do anything.

721
00:51:08,170 --> 00:51:11,540
Thanks for your help.
Our case almost had its statute expire.

722
00:51:26,221 --> 00:51:28,823
-Hey! What are you doing?
-Stop it!

723
00:51:28,890 --> 00:51:29,758
Stop, now!

724
00:51:30,759 --> 00:51:32,160
Stop!

725
00:51:37,432 --> 00:51:42,504
THE STATUTE IS ALMOST UP!
REQUESTING INFORMATION TO AID ARREST!

726
00:51:49,911 --> 00:51:51,379
You look just like it.

727
00:51:52,314 --> 00:51:53,248
What?

728
00:51:53,748 --> 00:51:54,783
Just take him away.

729
00:51:54,849 --> 00:51:55,684
Come on.

730
00:52:31,019 --> 00:52:34,456
The list of unidentified persons
in the Prefectural Police database.

731
00:52:47,669 --> 00:52:50,972
Why didn't they abolish
the statute of limitations for all cases?

732
00:52:55,443 --> 00:52:57,379
I just can't accept it.

733
00:52:58,046 --> 00:52:59,948
I haven't found him in there.

734
00:53:01,082 --> 00:53:03,084
-Please tell me.
-I have nothing to say.

735
00:53:03,151 --> 00:53:04,519
-Hey.
-I'm busy, go home.

736
00:53:04,586 --> 00:53:05,420
No!

737
00:53:05,487 --> 00:53:08,056
I'll come by again tonight.

738
00:53:08,123 --> 00:53:09,491
1995, APRIL 26

739
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:14,129
Where could he be?

740
00:53:17,465 --> 00:53:19,467
He may not be in Japan.

741
00:53:20,535 --> 00:53:21,603
But…

742
00:53:23,571 --> 00:53:25,607
He might be laughing somewhere out there.

743
00:53:29,778 --> 00:53:31,746
When I think about that…

744
00:53:35,784 --> 00:53:37,552
I can't sleep well.

745
00:53:40,588 --> 00:53:43,058
Why did they have to be killed?

746
00:53:47,862 --> 00:53:49,931
It's been 31 years already, huh.

747
00:53:56,404 --> 00:53:59,641
We’ve been tied to that day,
all this time.

748
00:54:20,962 --> 00:54:21,896
Hello?

749
00:54:22,464 --> 00:54:25,133
Are you still trying to identify
the former Makimura?

750
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:26,701
Community Safety is handling it.

751
00:54:27,569 --> 00:54:30,271
I reached someone who knows
that former Makimura guy.

752
00:54:31,439 --> 00:54:33,808
His real name is Jun Okochi.

753
00:54:35,710 --> 00:54:37,245
Why did he get a fake identity?

754
00:54:38,012 --> 00:54:39,047
Two years ago,

755
00:54:39,114 --> 00:54:42,117
he was exposed online for driving
a high school student to suicide.

756
00:54:43,485 --> 00:54:44,953
A digital tattoo, huh?

757
00:54:45,453 --> 00:54:48,590
By the way,
the student who committed suicide was…

758
00:55:01,169 --> 00:55:02,937
What’s wrong, Mr. Tagusari?

759
00:55:03,905 --> 00:55:05,006
Where is Nogami?

760
00:55:05,073 --> 00:55:07,675
Since it was a voluntary accompaniment,
I let him go.

761
00:55:08,243 --> 00:55:10,779
The man Nogami killed in the accident

762
00:55:10,845 --> 00:55:13,415
drove Nogami's son
to suicide two years ago!

763
00:55:13,481 --> 00:55:15,784
SAFE DRIVING
WATCH OUT FOR ROAD RAGE

764
00:55:17,652 --> 00:55:18,653
He’s gone!

765
00:55:21,756 --> 00:55:23,057
Search the area!

766
00:55:23,691 --> 00:55:25,393
It wasn't an unlucky accident.

767
00:55:31,199 --> 00:55:32,534
Maybe, from the start,

768
00:55:33,501 --> 00:55:35,570
he intended to kill him.

769
00:55:35,637 --> 00:55:41,609
MEN'S 100M SWIMMING CONTEST
OKI NOGAMI

770
00:55:50,919 --> 00:55:51,820
Hello.

771
00:55:51,886 --> 00:55:54,823
Someone saw a person
looking like Nogami on Asahina Street.

772
00:56:20,482 --> 00:56:22,083
Nogami!

773
00:56:25,720 --> 00:56:27,288
Nogami's motive is revenge.

774
00:56:27,355 --> 00:56:29,457
His moves are too unpredictable.

775
00:56:29,524 --> 00:56:32,627
Did my dad really kill someone?

776
00:56:32,694 --> 00:56:34,662
As revenge, it’s a job well done.

777
00:56:34,729 --> 00:56:35,697
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
